HR Analytics Dashboard

## 📌 Project Overview
This project is an interactive HR Analytics Dashboard built in Power BI.
It helps analyze employee attrition, workforce demographics, salary trends, job satisfaction,
and department-wise performance. The dashboard provides valuable insights to support HR 
decision-making and improve employee retention.

## 🎯 Project Objective

The objective of this project is to identify the key factors contributing to employee attrition
and provide meaningful insights through interactive visualizations.

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies Used

- Power BI
- Power Query
- DAX (Data Analysis Expressions)

## 📊 Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)

- Employee Count
- Attrition Count
- Attrition Rate
- Average Age
- Average Salary
- Average Years at Company.
  
## 📈 Dashboard Insights

- The highest attrition is observed in the 26–35 age group.
- Employees earning up to 5K show the highest attrition.
- Laboratory Technicians have the highest attrition among job roles.
- Life Sciences employees contribute the highest attrition by education.
- Job Satisfaction analysis helps identify employee engagement patterns.

## 🚀 Key Features

- Interactive Dashboard
- Department-wise Analysis
- Employee Attrition Analysis
- Salary & Age Analysis
- Job Satisfaction Report
- Easy-to-understand Visualizations
